subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
The following combination of characters distinguishes 

Parateleopus

from other ateleopodid genera: small mouth, posterior end of gape vertical to near anterior nostril (
Fig. 1A
); gill membranes united ventrally and attached to isthmus by soft tissue (
Fig. 2A
); sphenotic has vertically oblong crescent-shaped protrusion from behind eye to posteroinferior region of orbit (
Fig. 3A
); pelvic fin stiff, relatively short, the tip extending to point anywhere between base and anterior half of pectoral fin (
Fig. 4B
); wide pelvic bone (
Fig. 6
).
